etsysMultiUser8021xMIB.name: etsysMultiUser8021xMIB

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB module.

etsysMultiUser8021xMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysMultiUser8021xMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP enterprise MIBs under Enterasys Networks' enterprise OID pertaining to Multi-User IEEE 802.1X authentication. This MIB is designed to supplement and be used in connection with the standard IEEE 802.1X-2001 MIB.

etsysMulti1xAccessEntityTable.name: etsysMulti1xAccessEntityTable
etsysMulti1xAccessEntityTable.description: The system and configuration information for all the Access Entities.

etsysMulti1xAccessEntityEntry.name: etsysMulti1xAccessEntityEntry
etsysMulti1xAccessEntityEntry.description: The system and configuration information for an individual Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeIndex.name: etsysMulti1xAeIndex
etsysMulti1xAeIndex.description: Indicates if this Access Entity is currently active.

etsysMulti1xAeActive.name: etsysMulti1xAeActive
etsysMulti1xAeActive.description: Indicates if this Access Entity is currently active.

etsysMulti1xAeState.name: etsysMulti1xAeState
etsysMulti1xAeState.description: The current value of the Access Entity state machine.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthState.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthState
etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

etsysMulti1xAeInitialize.name: etsysMulti1xAeInitialize
etsysMulti1xAeInitialize.description: The initialization control for this Access Entity. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Access Entity to be initialized. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialization has completed.

etsysMulti1xAeReauthenticate.name: etsysMulti1xAeReauthenticate
etsysMulti1xAeReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this Access Entity. Setting this attribute TRUE causes the Access Entity state machine to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

etsysMulti1xAeReAuthPeriod.name: etsysMulti1xAeReAuthPeriod
etsysMulti1xAeReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

etsysMulti1xAeSupplicantAddress.name: etsysMulti1xAeSupplicantAddress
etsysMulti1xAeSupplicantAddress.description: The MAC address that this Access Entity is currently bound to.

etsysMulti1xAeUserName.name: etsysMulti1xAeUserName
etsysMulti1xAeUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsTable.name: etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsTable
etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsTable.description: The statistics objects for the all the Access Entities.

etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsEntry.name: etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsEntry
etsysMulti1xAccessEntityStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an individual Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesTx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesTx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolStartFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolStartFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolLogoffFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespIdFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqIdFramesTx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqFramesTx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqFramesTx
etsysMulti1xAeEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeInvalidEapolFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Access Entity in which the frame type is not recognized.

etsysMulti1xAeEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapLengthErrorFramesRx
etsysMulti1xAeEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Access Entity in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameVersion.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameVersion
etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameSource.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameSource
etsysMulti1xAeEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

etsysMulti1xAeDiagEntry.description: The diagnostics information for an individual Access Entity.

etsysMulti1xAeEntersConnecting.name: etsysMulti1xAeEntersConnecting
etsysMulti1xAeEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to the CONNECTING state from any other state.

etsysMulti1xAeEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.name: etsysMulti1xAeEapLogoffsWhileConnecting
etsysMulti1xAeEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to DISCONNECTED as a result of receiving an EAPOL-Logoff message.

etsysMulti1xAeEntersAuthenticating.name: etsysMulti1xAeEntersAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysMulti1xAeAuthSuccessWhileAuthentica.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthSuccessWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

etsysMulti1xAeAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentic.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication timeout (authTimeout = TRUE).

etsysMulti1xAeAuthFailWhileAuthenticatin.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthFailWhileAuthenticatin.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating
etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
etsysMulti1xAeAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.name: etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
etsysMulti1xAeAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendResponses.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendResponses
etsysMulti1xAeBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendAccessChallenges.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendAccessChallenges
etsysMulti1xAeBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
etsysMulti1xAeBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendNonNakResponsesFrom.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
etsysMulti1xAeBackendNonNakResponsesFrom.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthSuccesses.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthSuccesses
etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthFails.name: etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthFails
etsysMulti1xAeBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aFail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

etsysMulti1xSessionStatsTable.name: etsysMulti1xSessionStatsTable

etsysMulti1xSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics for an individual Access Entity. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each Access Entity where there is no session currently active.

etsysMulti1xSessionFramesTx.name: etsysMulti1xSessionFramesTx
etsysMulti1xSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted on this port for this session.

etsysMulti1xSessionId.name: etsysMulti1xSessionId
etsysMulti1xSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

etsysMulti1xSessionAuthenticMethod.name: etsysMulti1xSessionAuthenticMethod
etsysMulti1xSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

etsysMulti1xSessionTime.name: etsysMulti1xSessionTime

etsysMulti1xSessionTerminateCause.name: etsysMulti1xSessionTerminateCause
etsysMulti1xSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

etsysMulti1xSessionUserName.name: etsysMulti1xSessionUserName
etsysMulti1xSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

etsysMulti1xSessionActive.name: etsysMulti1xSessionActive
etsysMulti1xSessionActive.description: Indicates if this session is currently active.

etsysMulti1xUserNameIndex.description: The fixed length equivalent of the etsysMulti1xUserName object. When the length of the corresponding etsysMulti1xUserName object is less then 8 octets this object is padded with null octets. When the length of the corresponding etsysMulti1xUserName object is greater than 8 octets this object has the value of the etsysMulti1xUserName object truncated to 20 octets.
